+ JOB Card Format (1)
} The JOB Card is spread over five lines, followed by three comment
} lines. The JOB Card lines are as follows:-
}
}   Line 1.  The Jobname, "JOB", and the account field.  The latter has
}   sub-fields.  The first is normally the user's logonid, but for borou
}   ad hoc work submitted by LOLA, will be a borough code (see PCG).  Th
}   second sub-field is the application code.
}
}   For LOLA in-house work, these fields are not currently used for char
}   but a distribution code is derived from the first, logonid, sub-fiel
}   (1st, 3rd and 4th letters, = LOLA group) and will be printed on the
}   separator of the job's SYSOUT.
}
}   The Jobname is the LOLA standard for in-house work.
}
                        +For more information press%ENTER}
